<subSubSection box="[103,337,671,695]" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" type="multiple">
<paragraph blockId="3.[102,753,671,1054]" box="[103,337,671,695]" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">
<emphasis box="[103,337,671,695]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">Taxonomic discussion</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="184" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[102,753,671,1054]" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">
Based on the description (
<bibRefCitation author="GUSSONE" box="[421,588,710,734]" firstAuthor="GUSSONE" journalOrPublisher="Napoli" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" refId="ref3281" refString="GUSSONE, G. (1844). Florae siculae synopsis exhibens plantas vasculares inSiciliainsulisque adjacentibus huc usque detectas secundum systema linneanum depositas 2. Napoli." title="Florae siculae synopsis exhibens plantas vasculares inSiciliainsulisque adjacentibus huc usque detectas secundum systema linneanum depositas 2" type="book" year="1844">GUSSONE, 1844</bibRefCitation>
) and the specimens collected by G. Gussone, 
<taxonomicName box="[434,555,742,766]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis box="[434,555,742,766]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A. elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be included in sect. 
<taxonomicName authority="Dumort." authorityName="Dumort." box="[157,371,774,798]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Teutliopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[157,272,774,798]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">Teutliopsis</emphasis>
Dumort.
</taxonomicName>
, the taxa of which arecharacterized by the presence of herbaceous or cartilaginoid fruiting bracts, which are indistinctly veined and have more or less dentate margins (
<bibRefCitation author="AELLEN" box="[205,363,870,894]" editor="HEGI, G." firstAuthor="AELLEN" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" pagination="664 - 693" part="2" refId="ref2461" refString="AELLEN, P. (1960). Atriplex L. In: HEGI, G. (ed.), Ill. Fl. MittelEur. ed. 2, 3: 664 - 693." title="Atriplex L" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Ill. Fl. MittelEur." year="1960">AELLEN, 1960</bibRefCitation>
). In particular, 
<taxonomicName box="[526,651,870,894]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis box="[526,651,870,894]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A. elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be related to 
<taxonomicName authority="DC." authorityName="DC." box="[237,413,902,926]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="prostrata">
<emphasis box="[237,363,902,926]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A. prostrata</emphasis>
DC.
</taxonomicName>
[the rejected name 
<taxonomicName box="[618,723,902,926]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hastata">
<emphasis box="[618,723,902,926]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A. hastata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. was often misapplied to this species (
<bibRefCitation author="TURLAND" box="[493,662,934,958]" firstAuthor="TURLAND" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" pagination="325" part="45" refId="ref3675" refString="TURLAND, N. (1996). 1224. Proposal toreject the nameAtriplex hastataL. (Chenopodiaceae). Taxon 45: 325." title="Proposal toreject the nameAtriplex hastataL. (Chenopodiaceae)" type="journal article" year="1996">TURLAND, 1996</bibRefCitation>
), but the name 
<taxonomicName box="[166,272,966,990]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hastata">
<emphasis box="[166,182,966,990]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[195,272,966,990]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">hastata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its strict sense refers to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Rafn) Fries" authorityName="Fries" authorityYear="1845" baseAuthorityName="Rafn" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calotheca">
<emphasis box="[547,563,966,990]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[576,678,966,990]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">calotheca</emphasis>
(Rafn) Fries
</taxonomicName>
, growing along coasts of West and North Europe], to 
<taxonomicName box="[102,200,1030,1054]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="patula">
<emphasis box="[102,200,1030,1054]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A. patula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. and to 
<taxonomicName authority="Sukhor." authorityName="Sukhor." box="[302,509,1030,1054]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nilotica">
<emphasis box="[302,413,1030,1054]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A. nilotica</emphasis>
Sukhor.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[102,753,1070,1549]" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">
<taxonomicName box="[140,328,1070,1094]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="prostrata">
<emphasis box="[140,328,1070,1094]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">Atriplex prostrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="CANDOLLE" box="[520,753,1070,1094]" firstAuthor="CANDOLLE" journalOrPublisher="Paris" page="387" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" refId="ref2684" refString="CANDOLLE, A. - P. (1805). Fl. Franc. 3. Paris." title="Fl. Franc. 3" type="book" year="1805">CANDOLLE (1805: 387</bibRefCitation>
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">“[…] long du canal de Saint-Valery […] aux environs du Hâvre”</emphasis>
).According tothe protologue, thisspecies ischaracterized by leaves with prominent lateral lobes and fruiting bractswithout tubercules or spines on the dorsal surface. The lectotypification of 
<taxonomicName box="[324,457,1230,1254]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="prostrata">
<emphasis box="[324,457,1230,1254]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A. prostrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was made by 
<bibRefCitation author="GUSTAFSSON" firstAuthor="GUSTAFSSON" journalOrPublisher="Opera Bot." pageId="3" pageNumber="184" pagination="1 - 63" part="39" refId="ref3308" refString="GUSTAFSSON, M. (1976). Evolutionary trends in the Atriplex prostrata group of Scandinavia. Taxonomy and morphological variation. Opera Bot. 39: 1 - 63." title="Evolutionary trends in the Atriplex prostrata group of Scandinavia. Taxonomy and morphological variation" type="journal article" year="1976">GUSTAFSSON (1976)</bibRefCitation>
on a specimen kept in G. The same author gives a detailed description of the species, and as to the fruiting bracts, he indicates that they have “[…] the back from smooth to dentate […]”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[102,753,1070,1549]" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">
<taxonomicName box="[140,301,1397,1421]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="patula">
<emphasis box="[140,301,1397,1421]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">Atriplex patula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="LINNAEUS" box="[500,746,1397,1421]" firstAuthor="LINNAEUS" journalOrPublisher="Stockholm" page="1053" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" refId="ref3417" refString="LINNAEUS, C. (1753). Species Plantarum 2. Stockholm." title="Species Plantarum 2" type="book" year="1753">LINNAEUS (1753:1053)</bibRefCitation>
<emphasis box="[103,419,1429,1453]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">“in Europae cultis, ruderatis”</emphasis>
as 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">
“ 
<taxonomicName box="[460,585,1429,1453]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">ATRIPLEX</taxonomicName>
caule herbaceo patulo, foliis subdeltoideo-lanceolatis, calycibus feminum dicto dentatis”
</emphasis>
and lectotypified two centuries later by 
<bibRefCitation author="TASCHEREAU" firstAuthor="TASCHEREAU" journalOrPublisher="Canad. J. Bot." pageId="3" pageNumber="184" pagination="1571 - 1594" part="50" refId="ref3644" refString="TASCHEREAU, P. M. (1972). Taxonomyand distribution of A triplex species inNova Scotia. Canad. J. Bot. 50: 1571 - 1594." title="Taxonomyand distribution of A triplex species inNova Scotia" type="journal article" year="1972">TASCHEREAU (1972)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[102,754,1565,1909]" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">
Several authors (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="AELLEN" box="[363,516,1565,1589]" editor="TUTIN, T. G." firstAuthor="AELLEN" journalOrPublisher="Cambridge UniversityPress" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" pagination="95 - 97" part="1" refId="ref2499" refString="AELLEN, P. (1964). Atriplex L. In: TUTIN, T. G. &amp; al. (ed.), Fl. Eur. 1: 95 - 97. Cambridge UniversityPress." title="Atriplex L." type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Fl. Eur." year="1964">AELLEN, 1964</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="PIGNATTI" box="[526,690,1565,1589]" firstAuthor="PIGNATTI" journalOrPublisher="EdAgricole" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" refId="ref3512" refString="PIGNATTI, S. (1982). Fl. Ital. 1. EdAgricole." title="Fl. Ital. 1" type="book" year="1982">PIGNATTI, 1982</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="CASTROVIEJO" editor="CASTROVIEJO, S." firstAuthor="CASTROVIEJO" journalOrPublisher="Real JardinBotanico, Madrid" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" pagination="503 - 513" part="2" refId="ref2719" refString="CASTROVIEJO, S. (1990). Atriplex L. In: CASTROVIEJO, S. &amp; al. (ed.), Fl. Iber. 2: 503 - 513. Real JardinBotanico, Madrid." title="Atriplex L." type="journal article" volumeTitle="Fl. Iber." year="1990">CASTROVIEJO,1990</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="AKEROYD" box="[273,447,1597,1621]" editor="TUTIN, T. G." firstAuthor="AKEROYD" journalOrPublisher="Cambridge UniversityPress." pageId="3" pageNumber="184" pagination="115 - 117" part="2" refId="ref2539" refString="AKEROYD, J. R. (1993). Atriplex L. In: TUTIN, T. G. &amp; al. (ed.), Fl. Eur. ed. 2, 1: 115 - 117. Cambridge UniversityPress." title="Atriplex L." type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Fl. Eur" year="1993">AKEROYD,1993</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="TAN, K." box="[458,573,1597,1621]" editor="STRID, A. &amp; K. T AN" journalOrPublisher="KoeltzScientificBooks" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" pagination="121 - 126" part="1" refId="ref3605" refString="TAN, K. (1997). Atriplex L. In: STRID, A. &amp; K. T AN (ed.), Fl. Hellen. 1: 121 - 126. KoeltzScientificBooks." title="Atriplex L" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Fl. Hellen." year="1997">T AN,1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="JONSELL, B." box="[584,742,1597,1621]" journalOrPublisher="Swedish Royal Academyof Sciences, Stockolm" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" refId="ref3393" refString="JONSELL, B. (ed.) (2001). Fl. Nordica 2. Swedish Royal Academyof Sciences, Stockolm." title="Fl. Nordica 2" type="book" year="2001">J ONSELL,2001</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="WELSH" box="[103,255,1629,1653]" editor="FLORA OF NORTH AMERICA EDITORIAL COMMITTEE" firstAuthor="WELSH" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" pagination="322 - 381" refId="ref3700" refString="WELSH, S. L. (2003). Atriplex L. In: FLORA OF NORTH AMERICA EDITORIAL COMMITTEE (ed.), Fl. N. Amer. 4: 322 - 381." title="Atriplex L" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Fl. N. Amer. 4" year="2003">WELSH, 2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="GELIN" box="[266,467,1629,1653]" editor="WU, Z. Y." etAl="&amp; al." firstAuthor="GELIN" journalOrPublisher="Science Press." pageId="3" pageNumber="184" pagination="362 - 363" part="5" refId="ref3136" refString="GELIN, Z., S. L. M OSYAKIN &amp; S. E. C LEMANTS (2003). Atriplex L. In: WU, Z. Y. &amp; al. (ed.), Fl. China 5: 362 - 363. Science Press." title="Atriplex L" type="journal article" volumeTitle="Fl. China" year="2003">GELIN &amp; al., 2003</bibRefCitation>
) considered these species morphologically related, highlighting leaf base features (truncate in 
<taxonomicName box="[226,350,1693,1717]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="prostrata">
<emphasis box="[226,350,1693,1717]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A. prostrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. cuneate in 
<taxonomicName box="[503,598,1693,1717]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="patula">
<emphasis box="[503,598,1693,1717]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A. patula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) as diagnostic. The examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[347,401,1725,1749]" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">types</typeStatus>
(kept in G and LINN) and several other specimens (see the 
<emphasis box="[373,532,1757,1781]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">specimina visa</emphasis>
) allowed to confirm that this is the only character-state marking the two species. The fruiting bracts are very variable (both in margins and in dorsal surface) and they cannot be used to separate 
<taxonomicName box="[629,753,1853,1877]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="prostrata">
<emphasis box="[629,753,1853,1877]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A. prostrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName box="[161,258,1885,1909]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="patula">
<emphasis box="[161,258,1885,1909]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A. patula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[827,1479,281,728]" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">
Recently, the new species 
<taxonomicName box="[1134,1240,281,305]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nilotica">
<emphasis box="[1134,1240,281,305]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A. nilotica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(included in sect. 
<taxonomicName authority="Sukhor." authorityName="Sukhor." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Teutliopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">Teutliopsis</emphasis>
Sukhor.
</taxonomicName>
) was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="SUKHORUKOV" box="[1196,1419,313,337]" firstAuthor="SUKHORUKOV" journalOrPublisher="Feddes Repert." pageId="3" pageNumber="184" pagination="32 - 37" part="121" refId="ref3528" refString="SUKHORUKOV, A. P. (2010). Atriplex nilotica Sukhor. (sect. Teutiliopsis, Chenopodiaceae) - eine neue Art fur dieagyptische Flora. Feddes Repert. 121: 32 - 37." title="Atriplex nilotica Sukhor. (sect. Teutiliopsis, Chenopodiaceae) - eine neue Art fur dieagyptische Flora" type="journal article" year="2010">SUKHORUKOV (2010)</bibRefCitation>
from 
<emphasis box="[828,1182,345,369]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">“Aegyptia, Assuan, ad Nili ripas”</emphasis>
. Based on the diagnosis and the examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[1075,1171,377,401]" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">holotype</typeStatus>
, thisspecies ischaracterized in having the leaves withbase cuneateand margins repandodentate and the fruiting bracts clearly tuberculate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[827,1479,281,728]" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">
The found specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[1119,1237,480,504]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis box="[1119,1237,480,504]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A. elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have the fruiting bracts with smooth dorsal surface and proximally entire or dentate margins. The leaves are mostly entire with a cuneate base; only few of them (in the upper part) have two not prominent lateral lobes and obtuse (not truncate) base. Even 
<bibRefCitation author="GUSSONE" box="[1298,1479,608,632]" firstAuthor="GUSSONE" journalOrPublisher="Napoli" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" refId="ref3281" refString="GUSSONE, G. (1844). Florae siculae synopsis exhibens plantas vasculares inSiciliainsulisque adjacentibus huc usque detectas secundum systema linneanum depositas 2. Napoli." title="Florae siculae synopsis exhibens plantas vasculares inSiciliainsulisque adjacentibus huc usque detectas secundum systema linneanum depositas 2" type="book" year="1844">GUSSONE (1844)</bibRefCitation>
indicates 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">“[…] foliis deltoideo-oblongis, infimis hastatis oppositis (paucis) […]”</emphasis>
[leaves deltoid-oblong, the lower ones hastate opposite (few)].
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[828,1479,744,1127]" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">
Based on these observations, 
<taxonomicName box="[1172,1291,744,768]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis box="[1172,1291,744,768]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A. elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be more related with 
<taxonomicName box="[978,1086,776,800]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="patula">
<emphasis box="[978,1086,776,800]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A. patula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although Italian floras (
<bibRefCitation author="FIORI, A. &amp; G. P AOLETTI" journalOrPublisher="Padova" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" part="1" refId="ref3113" refString="FIORI, A. &amp; G. P AOLETTI (1896 - 1898). Fl. Analitica Italia 1. Padova." title="Fl. Analitica Italia" type="journal volume" year="1896">FIORI &amp; PAOLETTI, 1896-1898</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="FIORI" box="[1063,1187,808,832]" firstAuthor="FIORI" journalOrPublisher="Firenze" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" refId="ref3095" refString="FIORI, A. (1925). Nuova Fl. Analitica Ital. 1. Firenze." title="Nuova Fl. Analitica Ital" type="book" year="1925">FIORI, 1925</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="ZANGHERI" box="[1197,1370,808,832]" firstAuthor="ZANGHERI" journalOrPublisher="Cedam, Padova" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" refId="ref3738" refString="ZANGHERI, P. (1976). Fl. Ital. 1. Cedam, Padova." title="Fl. Ital. 1" type="book" year="1976">ZANGHERI, 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="PIGNATTI" firstAuthor="PIGNATTI" journalOrPublisher="EdAgricole" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" refId="ref3512" refString="PIGNATTI, S. (1982). Fl. Ital. 1. EdAgricole." title="Fl. Ital. 1" type="book" year="1982">PIGNATTI, 1982</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation author="GREUTER" box="[940,1170,840,864]" etAl="&amp; al." firstAuthor="GREUTER" journalOrPublisher="ConservatoireetJardinbotaniquesdeGeneve" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" part="1" refId="ref3217" refString="GREUTER, W., H. BURDET &amp; G. LONG (ed.) (1984). Med-checklist. Pteridophyta, Gymnospermae, Dicotyledones (Acanthaceae- Cneoraceae) 1. ConservatoireetJardinbotaniquesdeGeneve." title="Med-checklist. Pteridophyta, Gymnospermae, Dicotyledones (Acanthaceae- Cneoraceae)" type="journal volume" year="1984">GREUTER &amp; al. (1984)</bibRefCitation>
suggest affinity with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="prostrata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A. prostrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Regarding 
<taxonomicName box="[1007,1115,872,896]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nilotica">
<emphasis box="[1007,1115,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A. nilotica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1128,1249,872,896]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis box="[1128,1249,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A. elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from it in having leaves with entire margins and fruiting bracts with smooth dorsal surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[828,1479,744,1127]" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">
Another feature reported in literature to distinguish 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A. elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the leafless inflorescences (see e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="PIGNATTI" box="[1299,1467,1007,1031]" firstAuthor="PIGNATTI" journalOrPublisher="EdAgricole" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" refId="ref3512" refString="PIGNATTI, S. (1982). Fl. Ital. 1. EdAgricole." title="Fl. Ital. 1" type="book" year="1982">PIGNATTI, 1982</bibRefCitation>
). This character seems to be inconstant (leaves are lacking or are present in the proximal part of the inflorescences both in 
<taxonomicName box="[828,951,1103,1127]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis box="[828,951,1103,1127]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A. elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[958,1055,1103,1127]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="patula">
<emphasis box="[958,1055,1103,1127]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A. patula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1114,1242,1103,1127]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="prostrata">
<emphasis box="[1114,1242,1103,1127]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="184">A. prostrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
